These antibody tests could be critical to reopening the U.S., informing public health and state officials on how and when Americans can resume everyday activities.
Chan School of Public Health, said data from such serologic tests, as they are called, is sorely needed.
A best-case scenario would yield studies from accurate testing that inform public health and elected officials on when to relax state-at-home orders.
Simple antibody tests targeting COVID-19 might cross-react with other pathogens, such as the coronavirus that causes the common cold.
The plan will need antibody testing, “more testing, faster testing than we now have, and we’re going to need federal help,” Cuomo said.